<!--
    ServiceNow Update Set record-definition for the `sys_report` row that
    declares the "My Open Cases" list report on the `x_[scope]_case`
    custom table inside the scoped application `x_[scope]`.

    Per AAP Section 0.5.1 (File-by-File Transformation Plan) verbatim:
        servicenow-case-management-poc/reports/x_[scope]_my_open_cases.xml
            CREATE  Source: -
            Key Changes: "List report: status NOT IN (Resolved, Closed)
            AND assigned_agent = javascript:gs.getUserID()"

    Per AAP Section 0.4.1 (Refactored Structure Planning) verbatim:
        Agent Workspace Dashboard widget inventory includes
            "list widget for 'My open cases'"

    Per AAP Section 0.4.4 (User Interface Design) verbatim:
        Agent Workspace Dashboard - "list widget for 'My open cases'"

    Per AAP Section 0.7.3 (Validation Framework) verbatim, this report is
    one of the data sources for Gate 6 (Dashboards):
        "Both dashboards render with synthetic data ... All widgets display
         data; no broken report references"

    Per AAP Section 0.3.1 (Exhaustively In Scope) verbatim:
        servicenow-case-management-poc/reports/sys_report_x_[scope]_my_open_cases.xml
            "list of cases where assigned_agent = current user AND
             status NOT IN (Resolved, Closed)"

    THIS FILE'S ROLE IN THE OVERALL POC
    ===================================
    This is the agent's primary daily work queue - a personal list of
    cases assigned to the current viewer that are still actionable
    (not yet resolved or closed). It is consumed by the Agent Workspace
    Dashboard (../dashboards/pa_dashboards_x_[scope]_agent_workspace.xml)
    as a list widget, sitting alongside the "My Overdue Tasks" list
    widget and the "Case Count by Status" donut widget.

    Per-viewer semantics: when an agent loads the Agent Workspace
    dashboard, the platform invokes `gs.getUserID()` in the agent's
    session context, returning the agent's `sys_user.sys_id`. The
    encoded-query parser substitutes that sys_id into the filter clause
    `assigned_agent=...` and returns ONLY cases assigned to that user.
    No hardcoded user references are required, and the same report
    definition serves every viewer correctly per AAP Section 0.7.2
    "no hardcoded sys_id" constraint.

    SEMANTIC SOURCE-SIDE ANCHOR (READ-ONLY, NOT BYTE-FOR-BYTE PORTED)
    =================================================================
    ArkCase's case-domain "my queue" pattern is implemented across
    three Java service interfaces in the case-file-plugin:

      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/
        java/com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/model/CaseFile.java
        Lines 141-142:
            @Column(name = "cm_case_status")
            private String status;
        ArkCase tracks case status as a free-form String column on the
        `acm_case_file` MySQL table. The ServiceNow target normalizes
        this to a Choice field with exactly six values per AAP Section
        0.5.7 (Draft, Open, In Progress, Pending, Resolved, Closed)
        defined in ../choices/sys_choice_case_status.xml. The encoded-
        query `statusNOT INResolved,Closed` matches the Choice labels
        byte-for-byte in Title Case.

      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/
        java/com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/service/AcmQueueService.java
        Lines 37-40:
            public interface AcmQueueService {
                List<AcmQueue> listAllQueues();
            }
        ArkCase distributes case work via named Queues (intake, new,
        in-progress, etc.) - each case has a `cm_queue_id` foreign key
        and the UI provides per-queue list views. The ServiceNow target
        REPLACES the queue intermediate concept with a direct per-user
        `assigned_agent` reference field. This eliminates the queue
        as a separate domain entity and binds work distribution to
        identity rather than to a routing concept.

      - acm-plugins/acm-default-plugins/acm-case-file-plugin/src/main/
        java/com/armedia/acm/plugins/casefile/service/
        ActiveCaseFileByQueueService.java
        Lines 40-53: a Solr-backed facet query interface for "active
        cases per queue". The ServiceNow target REPLACES this with
        a native GlideRecord-backed list report (THIS file). Where
        ArkCase relied on Solr facet aggregates over the `cm_case_status`
        and `cm_queue_id` fields, the ServiceNow target uses a simple
        encoded-query filter that combines per-user identity equality
        with NOT-IN-terminal-status exclusion. There is no Solr in the
        target stack; the platform's GlideRecord layer is sufficient
        for a user-scope list of typically small cardinality (an
        agent's open case load).

      - "Active" semantic mapping: ArkCase considers a case "active"
        when its status is anything except a terminal value (the
        terminal value in ArkCase is encoded as the `closeDate` being
        non-null on the Disposition entity). The ServiceNow target's
        equivalent is `status NOT IN (Resolved, Closed)` per AAP
        Section 0.5.5 (state-machine transition map; Resolved and
        Closed are the post-Pending and terminal states respectively).

    DESIGN DECISIONS LOCKED IN BY THIS FILE
    =======================================
      - Aggregation discipline (AAP Section 0.5.1, this report's row):
        type = list. Per agent-prompt Rule 5, list reports leave
        <aggregate/>, <aggregation_source/>, <group_by/> empty. The
        rendered output is one row per matching record (NOT a count
        or grouped tally).

      - Field-list discipline (agent-prompt Rule 6 verbatim):
        <field_list>number,subject,priority,status,opened_date</field_list>.
        Five columns, comma-separated, no spaces, in display order:
          1. number       - auto-numbered identifier (CASE0000001 format
                            per AAP Section 0.7.4); read-only display
                            column linking back to the case form view.
          2. subject      - the case subject line (String 255 mandatory
                            per AAP Section 0.5.7). Truncated by the
                            list-view rendering if the column is narrow.
          3. priority     - Choice value from
                            ../choices/sys_choice_case_priority.xml
                            (Low, Medium, High, Critical). Allows the
                            agent to triage their queue at-a-glance.
          4. status       - Choice value from
                            ../choices/sys_choice_case_status.xml. Will
                            be one of Draft, Open, In Progress, Pending
                            because the filter excludes Resolved and
                            Closed.
          5. opened_date  - Auto-set DateTime (set by
                            ../business_rules/x_[scope]_set_opened_date.xml
                            on insert). Allows the agent to spot
                            stale cases.

        Intentionally OMITTED columns and rationale:
          - description: 4000-char free-form text per AAP Section
                         0.5.7. Rendering it in a dashboard list widget
                         consumes excessive horizontal space and
                         degrades at-a-glance scanning.
          - closed_date: always NULL for the rows returned by this
                         filter (Resolved and Closed are excluded), so
                         the column would be 100% empty.
          - assigned_group: redundant for the agent's view (they know
                            their group from context).
          - assigned_agent: constant across all rows in this report
                            (it is always the current viewer by virtue
                            of the filter); including it would waste
                            a column.
          - requester_name / requester_email: PII-shaped fields not
                                              needed for triage.

      - Filter discipline (agent-prompt Rule 4 verbatim):
            assigned_agent=javascript:gs.getUserID()
            ^statusNOT INResolved,Closed
        Two encoded-query clauses, AND-joined by `^`. Component-by-
        component analysis:
          - "assigned_agent" = field name (sys_user reference field
            on x_[scope]_case, defined in
            ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_assigned_agent.xml).
          - "=" = equality operator.
          - "javascript:gs.getUserID()" = dynamic-substitution token
            that the encoded-query parser resolves at evaluation time
            to the running user's sys_user.sys_id.
          - "^" = AND separator.
          - "statusNOT IN" = the "NOT IN" choice-list operator with
            no space between field name and operator, but a single
            ASCII space between "NOT" and "IN" - this is unique
            ServiceNow encoded-query syntax. Not "status NOT IN" with
            spaces around "NOT IN", and not "statusNOT_IN" or
            "statusNOTIN".
          - "Resolved,Closed" = comma-separated value list, no
            surrounding quotes, no spaces around the comma. Both
            values match the Choice labels in
            ../choices/sys_choice_case_status.xml byte-for-byte
            (Title Case).
        No `<` or `>` characters appear in this filter, so no XML
        entity escaping is required for the filter text. The `^`
        and `=` characters are XML-safe in element body content.

      - Why "NOT IN (Resolved, Closed)" instead of
        "IN (Draft, Open, In Progress, Pending)": both expressions
        produce equivalent result sets for the current six-status
        Choice list. NOT IN is the future-proof formulation: if a
        new status is added (e.g., "On Hold" or "Reopened") via a
        future Choice extension per AAP Section 0.5.7 ("Choices
        extensible"), it would automatically be treated as "open"
        without requiring a report modification. This authoring
        choice trades a microscopic query-cost difference for
        long-term maintainability.

      - Per-viewer semantics: the report definition is identical
        regardless of which user runs it; the platform's encoded-
        query parser substitutes `gs.getUserID()` at evaluation time,
        so each viewer sees only their own assigned cases. This is
        the ServiceNow-native equivalent of ArkCase's per-user queue
        view without requiring per-user report duplication.

      - ACL interaction: the table-level READ ACL on x_[scope]_case
        controls which rows the user CAN see in principle; this
        report's filter further narrows to "MY assigned ones." For
        a `case_agent` (assigned-only ACL per AAP Section 0.5.6),
        this is doubly-restrictive (ACL: assigned only; filter:
        assigned to me). For a `case_manager` (all-access ACL), the
        ACL allows full read but the filter still narrows to "my
        assigned." For a `case_viewer` (read-only all-access ACL),
        the filter narrows to cases where the viewer happens to be
        `assigned_agent` (typically zero, since viewers are not
        normally assignees).

      - Scope binding: <sys_scope>x_[scope]</sys_scope> and
        <sys_package source="x_[scope]">x_[scope]</sys_package>
        bind THIS record to the same scoped-app row that the parent
        sys_app record (../app/sys_app/x_[scope]_case_management.xml)
        publishes. Cross-file consistency: the sibling reports
        (x_[scope]_avg_time_to_close.xml, x_[scope]_my_overdue_tasks.xml,
        and the other five) use identical scope-reference values,
        ensuring all eight reports resolve to the same sys_app row
        at preview time. Reference-by-name not reference-by-sys_id
        per AAP Section 0.7.2 (no hardcoded sys_ids constraint).

      - <sys_id> determinism: the value
        ee04fa982b136ad35c6fe1512826f6ab is the lowercase MD5 of the
        canonical record name "x_[scope]_my_open_cases". This matches
        the scope-wide convention documented in
        ../reports/x_[scope]_avg_time_to_close.xml lines 236-247
        (md5("x_[scope]_case") = bd806f5b23883f5d28ed792570f1070b;
         md5("x_[scope]_case_manager") = 73710b052f274ece1d578c00f4424423;
         md5("x_[scope]_avg_time_to_close") = 79fabb5f5754b629205b2382face3ebb).
        Deterministic derivation makes the Update Set re-importable
        on a fresh PDI without sys_id collisions: re-importing the
        same XML on the same or any future PDI resolves the same
        sys_id and idempotently updates the same report row rather
        than creating a duplicate. This stability is REQUIRED because
        the Agent Workspace dashboard
        (../dashboards/pa_dashboards_x_[scope]_agent_workspace.xml)
        references THIS report by `<name>x_[scope]_my_open_cases</name>`,
        and the dashboard widget binding must resolve consistently
        across re-imports.

    CROSS-DEPENDENCY GRAPH
    ======================
    DEPENDS ON (must load earlier in the Update Set):
      - ../app/sys_app/x_[scope]_case_management.xml
      - ../app/sys_scope/x_[scope].xml
      - ../tables/x_[scope]_case.xml                  (parent table)
      - ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_assigned_agent.xml
            (defines the reference field used in the user-equality
             filter clause)
      - ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_status.xml
            (defines the Choice field used in the NOT IN filter clause)
      - ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_number.xml
      - ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_subject.xml
      - ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_priority.xml
      - ../dictionary/x_[scope]_case_opened_date.xml
            (the four dictionary entries above define the columns
             rendered in the list)
      - ../choices/sys_choice_case_status.xml
            (defines the `Resolved` and `Closed` Choice values
             referenced in the filter; Title-Case match is mandatory)

    REFERENCED BY (must load later in the Update Set):
      - ../dashboards/pa_dashboards_x_[scope]_agent_workspace.xml
        References THIS report by `<name>x_[scope]_my_open_cases</name>`,
        NOT by sys_id, so a fresh-PDI re-import correctly resolves the
        widget binding to the deterministic MD5-derived sys_id above.

    SEED-DATA DEPENDENCY (Validation Gate 6 pass condition):
      - ../seed-data/users/sys_user_x_[scope]_demo_agent.xml must exist
        so that gs.getUserID() resolves to a real sys_user when the
        dashboard is run by the demo agent.
      - ../seed-data/cases/x_[scope]_case_demo_*.xml must include at
        least one case where:
          assigned_agent = demo_agent (resolved by user_name lookup
                          per AAP Section 0.7.2 no-hardcoded-sys_id)
          status         = Open OR In Progress OR Pending OR Draft
                          (i.e., NOT Resolved and NOT Closed)
        The ten demo cases per AAP Section 0.4.1 span all six statuses
        and both case types, so seed cases demo_02 (Open / General
        Inquiry), demo_03 (In Progress / General Inquiry), demo_04
        (Pending / General Inquiry), demo_07 (Open / Complaint), and
        demo_08 (In Progress / Complaint) are all eligible to satisfy
        this gate. Without at least one such seed case assigned to the
        demo agent, this report returns zero rows when rendered on the
        Agent Workspace dashboard, which would fail the "All widgets
        display data" criterion of Validation Gate 6 (AAP Section 0.7.3)
        even though the report DEFINITION itself is correct.

    UPDATE-SET ORDERING
    ===================
    Per AAP Section 0.5.2 (Cross-File Dependencies):
      - AFTER tables, dictionary, choices.
      - AFTER seed-data so that running the report yields non-empty
        results during validation.
      - BEFORE the Agent Workspace dashboard so that dashboard widget
        binding resolves.

    AUTHORING-RULES COMPLIANCE
    ==========================
      - AAP Section 0.7.2 verbatim:
          "No-hardcoded-sys_id constraint. Anywhere - flows, ACL
           conditions, scripts, seed data, UI Policies, UI Actions,
           Business Rules. Every cross-reference is resolved by
           GlideRecord lookup against a stable human-readable key
           (name, user_name, number, role_label)."
        This file: <sys_scope> and <sys_package> resolve by scope
        name; <sys_id> is THIS record's own primary key (not a
        hardcoded reference to another record). The `assigned_agent`
        comparison uses gs.getUserID() (dynamic), not a literal
        sys_user.sys_id. <table> resolves by table name. All compliant.

      - AAP Section 0.7.2 verbatim:
          "No-PII constraint. Synthetic data only."
        This file: report definition contains no PII; the report
        merely SELECTS rows from a table. Whatever PII or non-PII
        data is in those rows is the seed-data agent's responsibility
        to keep synthetic. The report definition is PII-free.

      - AAP Section 0.7.2 verbatim:
          "Scope-namespace exclusivity: every artifact ... must live
           in the auto-assigned `x_[scope]` namespace; zero global-
           scope writes are permitted."
        This file: <name> is `x_[scope]_my_open_cases`; <table> is
        `x_[scope]_case`; <sys_scope> and <sys_package> bind to the
        scoped app. Zero global-scope writes.

      - AAP Section 0.7.4 verbatim:
          "Auto-numbering format: the case `number` field MUST use
           format `CASE0000001` (7-digit zero-padded) and be Read-only."
        This file: column 1 (`number`) renders the case auto-number
        in CASE0000001 format per the x_[scope]_case auto-numbering
        definition in ../numbers/sys_number_x_[scope]_case.xml.

      - Agent-prompt Rule 8 (Per-Viewer Result Set):
        This file: filter uses `javascript:gs.getUserID()`. Each
        viewer sees ONLY their own assigned cases. There is no admin
        override at report level. ACLs further narrow what each role
        can see.

    VALIDATION CHECKLIST (mirrors agent-prompt verbatim)
    ====================================================
    [x] File path: servicenow-case-management-poc/reports/x_[scope]_my_open_cases.xml
    [x] Starts with <?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
